and operational decisions are effectively co-ordinated and consistently applied across the organization.Hires, directs, and coaches employees reporting to this position, and reviews employee performance on a continuing basis.Assists in planning and developing the construction of Library facilities, and monitors the operation and maintenance of such facilities.Manages the long-term planning and evaluation of public service delivery.Prepares, administers and co-ordinates budgets, ensuring that expenditures are effectively maintained and controlled.Forms strategic partnerships with community organizations to enhance service and advance the Library’s goals.Communicates and maintains an effective working relationship with the Library Board and staff, City personnel, representatives of other Library organisations, government agencies, and community organizations.Represents the Library in various community and civic activities.Co-ordinates committees and special projects to advance the Library’s goals. Prepares reports and correspondence on projects and policy matters.Investigates complaints related to public services and resolves by taking appropriate action.Provides mentorship and development opportunities to staff reporting to this position.Oversees employee discipline ranging from verbal and written warnings and suspension, up to and including discharge.Represents Management’s interests in Labour Relations matters such as Collective Bargaining, Labour Management Committee, and Job Evaluation Committee.Interprets, upholds and proposes changes to the terms and conditions of the Collective Agreement.Acts for the Chief Librarian in their absence.Performs other related duties. Qualifications, Knowledge, and Skills Master of Library Science from an A.L.A. accredited university program.Ten years or more progressive experience as a librarian and library leader.Experience working in a unionized workplace.Experience working with a Board of Directors is an asset.Knowledge of developments in public library service, including trends related to technology, artificial intelligence, library as spaces for content creation, and community building.Experience working with diverse communities and developing services to meet a variety of needs.Excellent leadership and management skills, with ability to delegate and give clear direction diplomatically.Strong project management skills, with experience in managing multiple initiatives under time constraints.Strong communication skills, comfortable with writing reports or presenting to large groups.Ability to influence with diplomacy to advance organizational goals. Ability to research and analyse subject matter, identify issues and trends, and generate summaries and recommendations.Ability to think creatively, implement new ideas, and champion change.Ability to build and enhance effective working relationships with staff and external contacts. Salary: $139,842 – 159,630 How to apply If you are interested in this opportunity, send your cover letter and resume with the subject “Director, Public Services” to SPLEmployment@surrey.ca. The deadline is Monday, January 29, 2023. We thank in advance all applicants who apply and advise that only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $139,842 – 159,630 Closes: 29 January, 2024 Surrey Libraries Surrey , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
