Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Coordinator, Technology Support Caledon , ON Description Caledon Public Library is a hub for discovery, innovation and inspiration. We nurture connections, collaboration and creativity and are situated within a dynamic municipality that successfully balances urban, rural and agricultural communities. With seven branches that serve as the cornerstones to the community, connecting people to information and each other is what we do!The OpportunityReporting to the Caledon Public Library’s Manager, Information Technology, the Coordinator, Technology Support is tasked with the provision of direct client support to library staff and, occasionally, members of public, by identifying, analyzing, resolving and documenting technology issues and requests for assistance, ensuring an exceptional customer service experience. This position is also responsible for the effective deployment, installation, configuration, operation, and maintenance of hardware including public and staff workstations, peripherals and related software applications. As a Coordinator, Technology Support, assigned duties will include but are not limited to:Provide professional customer service to internal IT clients by responding to and prioritizing requests for technology-related assistanceDevelop and maintain internal support tracking and resulting knowledge bases including frequently asked questions to aid in problem resolution Provide staff with guidance and recommendations in the appropriate use of hardware and software while promoting learning and improved self-relianceDeploy and image hardware, ensuring all devices are secured as per best practice and relevant library policiesInstall, maintain and upgrade computer hardware, software, drivers, and patchesMonitor hardware and network performance; troubleshooting, implementing and/or suggestion solutions as necessarySupport mobile connectivity devices, including hotspots and phones.Perform hardware repair for computer equipment and peripherals when necessary Maintains an accurate inventory of library technologiesDevelop and maintain accurate procedure manuals and other related documentationDevelop, maintain and support enterprise applications including SharePointThe Ideal CandidateWe are seeking an enthusiastic and passionate professional with a post-secondary degree or diploma in Computer Science or Information Technology, or equivalent combination of education and experience. Our ideal candidate has a minimum of 2 years related experience including help desk, hardware and system support and a Microsoft A+ certification. Practical experience and demonstrated computer proficiency in MS Office (Word, Excel, Outlook), Windows 10, SharePoint, IOS and Android devices. Demonstrated interest in emerging and maker technologies. Experience in Office365 would be an asset.This position offers a salary range of $68,350.55 to $82,513.23 plus a competitive benefit package.Satisfactory passing of a vulnerable sector check, and proof of qualifications will be required of any successful candidate(s) for this position.The Town is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to an inclusive and barrier-free workplace. If your application requires accommodation, please contact Human Resources at (905) 584-2272 Ext. 4738.Applications for this posting will be accepted until January 25, 2024 12:00PM.How To ApplyTo learn more about employment with the Town of Caledon and to apply for this exciting and challenging opportunity, visit: www.caledon.ca/careersIf needed and upon request, this document can be made available in an alternative format. Compensation $68,350.55&nbsp;to $82,513.23 Closes: 25 January, 2024 Caledon Public Library Caledon , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
