Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Information Clerk - Digital Studio - Regular Part-Time Burnaby , BC Description Burnaby Public Library is located on the ancestral and unceded homelands of the hən̓q̓əmin̓əm̓ and Sḵwx̱wú7mesh speaking peoples. We are grateful for the opportunity to work on this territory.Burnaby Public Library empowers the community to engage with and share stories, ideas and information. Our vision is a welcoming community where all people can explore, learn and connect. Burnaby is the third largest city in British Columbia, with excellent rapid transit links, significant parkland, and well-equipped recreational facilities. Our 250,000 residents speak 120 languages, and more than half of our culturally diverse population has a mother tongue other than English.BPL’s four libraries are important public spaces, meeting places and centres for discovery and dialogue, anchored by our broad and deep collections and our commitment to in-person service. BPL is changing to continue to meet the needs of our highly diverse community, with an increased emphasis on community-led approaches and connecting with people outside the library, a greater focus on digital literacy, and a commitment to upgrading and rethinking our public and staff spaces.__________________________________________________________________________________________ Burnaby Public Library (BPL) invites applications from all folks interested in part-time work as of Thursday January 11, 2024. Forward your resume and cover letter in confidence to careers@bpl.bc.ca and quote competition 2024-04.The closing date for this posting is Saturday January 20, 2024. Position Title:LIBRARY INFORMATION CLERK – 1 position Location:BOB PRITTIE METROTOWN LIBRARY (Digital Studio and Public Service Desks) AND CAMERON LIBRARY Status:REGULAR PART-TIME (benefits eligible) This position is located at the Metrotown Library’s Digital Studio and Public Service desks and at the Cameron Library. Position Summary: Library Information Clerks provide welcoming and inclusive service to people of all ages in Burnaby’s culturally diverse community. This position has a special focus on supporting users of the Metrotown Digital Studio and at the public service desks at the Metrotown and Cameron Libraries. Our ideal candidate is self-motivated and exhibits a strong team spirit and work ethic. They are innovative and flexible in a quickly changing library environment. It is important that they can use, demonstrate and learn different technologies, including computers, software and equipment for digital creation and design. While this position is based at the Bob Prittie Metrotown Library and Cameron Library, work may be required in any of our four library locations.Evening and weekend work will be required.The required schedules are included at the end of this posting. This position reports to the Digital Studio Coordinator. Duties: Welcomes and orients patrons to the Metrotown Digital Studio, Metrotown Library, Cameron Library, and library services and policies. Directs and helps patrons find library materials, assists them with their library accounts, and communicates our library services and policies.Performs circulation duties such as checking materials in and out; processing in-house, inter-branch and other library system requests by finding and placing items on hold; and creating new item requests. Demonstrates and helps patrons in the use of a variety of technology, including computers, scanners, self-service checkout machines, printers, recording equipment, and digitization tools; troubleshoots common problems with computers and equipment; reports issues as needed.Monitors the Digital Studio and its equipment; ensures appropriate use of hardware and software in accordance with library policy and license agreements. Answers questions about using our online resources, including downloadable and streaming digital content and mobile apps. Books library rooms, recording studios and studio stations for patrons, staff and groups, and communicates policies and procedures; helps patrons use equipment in the room. Gives basic readers’ advisory services to patrons; Responds to information questions and refers questions that need professional assistance to a librarian.Maintains patron accounts and collects library fees; carries out opening and closing cash procedures.Assists patrons with requests for items from another library system and how to submit a suggested purchase. May give direction to other staff if a supervisor is absent during your shift; helps with opening and closing the library; may help librarians in a program or workshop; may assist with training staff on equipment; maintain displays.Keeps records and statistics.You have Grade 12 education with some additional training, plus you have related library work experience. Or you have a mix of education, training and experience that’s similar.Ability and experience using language skills in addition to English to assist the public is a considerable asset.You are comfortable using computers and learning new technology and are able to troubleshoot common computer problems.You are knowledgeable and passionate about digital literacy and digital inclusion.You are curious about what library users and community members need, and you have a passion for delivering excellent customer service.You care about and want to apply equity, diversity, inclusion and anti-racism in your work. You show that you can work independently, creatively and flexibly in different situations with diverse people in our community. You use good judgment to make decisions and you can work with minimal supervision. You can maintain and update a variety of records, files and reference materials related to the work.You are able to give direction to other staff when a supervisor is absent, if needed. Qualifications: Salary:$29.48 to $35.15 hourly Hours: Evening and weekend work will be required. The current and extended Sunday schedules are included below. CURRENT (40hours biweekly) Week 1: Mon 1:45-8:15 Metrotown DS, Fri 10:15-6:15 Cameron, Sat 1-6 Metrotown PS Week 2: Mon 1:45-8:15 Metrotown DS, Wed 1-5 Metrotown DS, Sat 10:15-6:15 Cameron, Sun 12:15-5:15 Metrotown DS EXTENDED SUNDAYS approx. in spring 2024 (40hours biweekly) Week 1: Mon 12:15-8:15 Metrotown DS, Fri 10:15-6:15 Cameron, Sat 1-6 Metrotown PS Week 2: Mon 12:15-8:15 Metrotown DS, Sat 9-5 Cameron, Sun 10:15-6:15 Metrotown DS Schedules are subject to change to meet operational needs. All staff may be asked to work in other locations at any time. We thank all applicants for their interest in Burnaby Public Library. We encourage you to apply even if you do not have all the qualifications we list here. Only those selected for an interview will be contacted. BPL believes that diversifying our staff will make our organization better and more reflective of the community we serve. We encourage people of all genders, ages, ethnicities, cultures, abilities, sexual orientations, and life experiences to apply. Compensation $29.48 to $35.15 hourly Closes: 20 January, 2024 Burnaby Public Library Burnaby , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
